      <lg type="edition">
<l>āṭiya laḻaṟkuṭṭat</l>
<l>tāriru ḷaraiyiraviṉ</l>
<l>muṭappaṉaiyattu vērmutalāk</l>
<l>kaṭaikkuḷattuk kayaṅkāyap</l>
<l>paṅkuṉi yuyaraḻuvattut</l>
<l>talaināṇmī ṉilaitiriya</l>
<l>nilaināṇmī ṉataṉetirērtarat</l>
<l>toṉṉāṇmīṉ ṟuṟaipaṭiyap</l>
<l>pācic cellā tūci muṉṉā</l>
<l>taḷakkarttiṇai viḷakkākak</l>
<l>kaṉaiyeri parappak kāletirpu poṅki</l>
<l>yorumīṉ vīḻntaṉṟāl vicumpi ṉāṉē</l>
<l>yatukaṇ, ṭiyāmum piṟarum palvē ṟiravalar</l>
<l>paṟaiyicai yaruvi naṉṉāṭṭup poruna</l>
<l>ṉōyila ṉāyi ṉaṉṟumaṟ ṟilleṉa</l>
<l>vaḻinta neñca maṭiyuḷam parappa</l>
<l>vañciṉa meḻunāḷ vantaṉ ṟiṉṟē</l>
<l>maintuṭai yāṉai kaivait tuṟaṅkavun</l>
<l>tiṇpiṇi muracaṅ kaṇkiḻin turuḷavuṅ</l>
<l>kāval veṇkuṭai kālparin tulaṟavuṅ</l>
<l>kāliyaṟ kalimāk katiyila vaikavu</l>
<l>mēlō rulaka meytiṉa ṉākali</l>
<l>ṉoṇṟoṭi makaḷirk kuṟutuṇai yākit</l>
<l>taṉṟuṇai yāya maṟantaṉaṉ kollō</l>
<l>pakaivarp piṇikku māṟṟa ṉacaivark</l>
<l>kaḷantukoṭai yaṟiyā vīkai</l>
<l>maṇivarai yaṉṉa māa yōṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>In the middle of the night in difficult darkness, (2)</l>
<l>in a port of fire whose nature is dancing, (1)</l>
<l>while, with the root of the crooked palmyra tree as a base, (3)</l>
<l>the deep of the pond was hot to the limit, (4)</l>
<l>while in the high depth of Phalguni (5)</l>
<l>the star on the first day did not move from [its] position, (6)</l>
<l>while against it rose the star in the stable day, (7)</l>
<l>while the star on the old day sank into the ghat, (8)</l>
<l>not going east, not approaching north, (9)</l>
<l>as the lamp of the ocean clan (10)</l>
<l>while dense darkness spread, facing the time, boiling, (11)</l>
<l>a star fell down indeed from the sky. (12)</l>
<l>Seeing that, we and others [and] many different beggars (13)</l>
<l>said “the fighter of the good land with waterfalls that sound [like] drums, </l>
<l>if he were without pain it would be good”, (14f.)</l>
<l>[and] while desolate hearts spread in [our] constricted insides, (16)</l>
<l>seven days came with us in fear. Today, (17)</l>
<l>while the mighty elephant put down [its] trunk [and] slumbered, (18)</l>
<l>while the drum with taught straps tore [its] eye rolling, (19)</l>
<l>while the protective white parasol broke [its] handle [and] withered, (20)</l>
<l>while the spirited horses that move [like] the wind kept without motion, (21)</l>
<l>because he reachind the world of those above, (22)</l>
<l>being [now] the consort had by women with bright bracelets, (23)</l>
<l>did he forget the group of his own consorts? (24)</l>
<l>– the one dark like a sapphire mountain, (27)</l>
<l>[who was] giving [gifts] that did not know of giving by measure (26)</l>
<l>to those who yearned [for them], he capable of tying down the enemies. (25)  </l>
</lg>
